But the problem says "A B meaning A must be completed before B", and A and B are tasks, so they must be in the task names list.

Let's consider the time complexity again.
Heap push and pop take O(log N).
We push each task at most once, and pop each task at most once. So heap operations take O(N log N).
For each edge, we decrement in-degree and possibly push to heap. There are M edges, so this takes O(M log N) in the worst case (if every edge causes a push, which is impossible, but bounded by M log N).
Total time complexity is O((N + M) log N). This meets the requirement.

Space complexity is O(N + M) for the graph and heap.

I'm confident in this solution.
